It seems "Named Destinations" gonna break.

## Generate Source PDF

I'm using pdf generated by `pdflatex` with cross-refs inside. Here is the tex-file I use: 

```tex
\documentclass[a4paper]{article}
\usepackage{hyperref}
\newcounter{cnt}

\begin{document}

\par Alpha -- \pageref{a}
\par Beta -- \pageref{b}
\par Gamma -- \pageref{c}

\newpage
Alpha Page \refstepcounter{cnt}\label{a}
\newpage
Beta Page \refstepcounter{cnt}\label{b}
\newpage
Gamma Page \refstepcounter{cnt}\label{c}

\end{document}
```

And here is the `input.pdf` generated by `pdflatex`: [input.pdf](https://github.com/mstamy2/PyPDF2/files/1259416/input.pdf)
You can click on the numbers and go to the corresponding page, everything's fine.

## MCVE: PDF + Code

Next, I use the following python code:

```python
import PyPDF2

reader = PyPDF2.PdfFileReader(open("input.pdf", "rb"))
writer = PyPDF2.PdfFileWriter()

# Transfer pages
for page in reader.pages:
    writer.addPage(page)

# Transfer named destinations -- am I missing something?
for nd in reader.namedDestinations:
    print(nd)
    writer.addNamedDestinationObject(reader.namedDestinations[nd])

outputStream = open("output.pdf", "wb")
writer.write(outputStream)
outputStream.close()
```

## The Problem

I get the following output: [output.pdf](https://github.com/mstamy2/PyPDF2/files/1259415/output.pdf)


As you can see, links to pages 2 and 3 stop working, however, the last one works.

I tested this with different LaTeX-generated documents and the named destinations seem to break randomly (some of them survive, but the most fail). This issue is both for python 2 and 3.

